---
description: Rules for Streamlit app development
alwaysApply: false
---

For Streamlit app work:

UI :
- Keep the app simple and demo-friendly
- Prioritize clarity over visual complexity
- Use business-friendly language
- Use exactly two tabs: `Single Prediction` and `Batch Prediction`
- Prefer accessible, colorblind-friendly styling

Functionality:
- Load model artifacts from `artifacts/models/`
- Validate user inputs
- Handle missing or invalid values safely
- Avoid hardcoded machine-specific paths
- Fail gracefully with clear messages

The app should include:
- Single customer churn prediction
- Batch CSV prediction
- Model notes and limitations within the existing two-tab layout

Production simulation:
- Show model version when possible
- Add prediction timestamp when possible
- Save prediction logs to `artifacts/logs/`
- Provide a ready-to-use sample batch input file when the task asks for batch prediction